<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-911-996  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 911 996.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Nov 13 1989 v19 n5 p1(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IFRA '89: a good show gets better. (Inca-Fiej Research Associationtrade show)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT/><TEXT>IFRA '89: A Good Show Gets Better WE HAVE ALWAYS enjoyed the annual Europeannewspaper show sponsored by the Inca-Fiej Research Association (IFRA).andP;  Ithas a congenial atmosphere, an interesting assortment of exhibitors, apleasant crowd of attenders and some nice cities as hosts.andP;  But in recentyears, it has provided an extra advantage: it brings together the companiesthat are becoming the driving force behind innovation in the newspaper systemmarket.andM;This year's show, held in Amsterdam from Oct. 16 to 19, was highlighted by apromising new pagination system developed by Talbot to run on the Macintosh,a thrust into newspaper pagination and display ad creation by CCI Europe, anearly color system from GEMS of Cambridge, a classified pagination systemfrom Tele-Ekonomi, impressive progress in pagination by Funkinform, and manymore developments.andM;Although it isn't clear at this point how many of these products will evermake it to the United States, we think all readers will be interested inseeing the trends.andO;</TEXT></DOC>